cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR. 

The paper presents a computer-aided diagnosis system based on convolutional neural networks for breast cancer diagnosis using thermal images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of data pre-processing, data augmentation, and hyper-parameter optimization, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging and diagnosis, which suggests cs.MED (Medical Imaging) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the influence of database size, which is a common topic in information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category.
